    "content": "**YES** — move it to a standalone file.\n\nThis is exactly the same principle we applied to the Preface: do not pre-deliver what the reader should discover through experience. If the reader knows they will be asked \"What happened to your sense of absurdity across the three examples?\" before reading Essay 3, they will read Essay 3 with absurdity-tracking already activated. The experiential sequence is designed to produce recognition without priming — the reader should arrive at the cat example without having been told to monitor their own affective response. Delivering the questions afterward preserves the experimental conditions. This is the standby reader as philosophical experiment, and good experiments do not tell the subject what to look for."
